<!-- /wp:html -->
<!-- wp:heading {"style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"clamp(24px,2.6vw,32px)"}}} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" style="font-size:clamp(24px,2.6vw,32px)">Sources<span class="sr-accent-dot">.</span></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->
<!-- wp:paragraph {"fontSize":"base"} -->
<p class="has-base-font-size" style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;max-width:75ch;margin-top:8px">The figures and claims in this article come from here. These are primary sources, not summaries: open them and check for yourself.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->
<!-- wp:html -->
<ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:20px 0 0;border-top:1px solid var(--sr-bordo)"><li style="margin-top:16px;line-height:1.55"><a href="https://www.garanteprivacy.it/home/docweb/-/docweb-display/docweb/9677876" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Garante per la protezione dei dati personali (Italian data protection authority) — cookie and other tracking tools guidelines</a><span style="display:block;font-size:14.5px;color:var(--sr-grigio);margin-top:4px">Consent to profiling cookies must be collected before they fire, not after: the rule behind every compliant cookie banner.</span></li><li style="margin-top:16px;line-height:1.55"><a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/reg/2016/679/oj" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GDPR Regulation 2016/679 — EUR-Lex</a><span style="display:block;font-size:14.5px;color:var(--sr-grigio);margin-top:4px">Data minimisation at checkout, and more generally the obligations that kick in from the first order with personal data.</span></li><li style="margin-top:16px;line-height:1.55"><a href="https://baymard.com/checkout-usability" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Baymard Institute — Checkout Usability</a><span style="display:block;font-size:14.5px;color:var(--sr-grigio);margin-top:4px">Research on checkout usability, based on repeated user testing across the biggest e-commerce sites: where and why the cart gets abandoned.</span></li><li style="margin-top:16px;line-height:1.55"><a href="https://web.dev/articles/vitals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">web.dev — Web Vitals</a><span style="display:block;font-size:14.5px;color:var(--sr-grigio);margin-top:4px">The official Core Web Vitals thresholds: why a slow e-commerce site loses customers before it even loses rankings.</span></li></ul>
<!-- /wp:html -->
